      "evidence_level": "DIRECT_TEXT_SOURCE_CALCULATION",
      "capture_text": "The paper reports CP-Ti/MWCNT compression data for three 0.5 wt.% and three 1.0 wt.% composite batches. The unreinforced matrix yield strength is 695 MPa. Composite yield strengths are 822, 782, 920, 800, 610, and 860 MPa. The source assigns thermal-mismatch strengthening of 159 MPa at 0.5 wt.% (0.86 vol.%) and 225 MPa at 1.0 wt.% (1.72 vol.%). Several source-budget shares exceed 100%, and the 1.0 wt.%-Batch-2 specimen weakens by 85 MPa while retaining a positive thermal-mismatch term; therefore these terms are retained as red-team source calculations rather than causal mechanism fractions.",
