      "evidence_level": "DIRECT_TEXT_SOURCE_CALCULATION",
      "capture_text": "The paper compares 0.5 wt.% CNT/Ti materials made through RM or PBM powder treatment and SPS or cold-compaction routes followed by hot extrusion. Matched Ti controls are 434 MPa for SPS and 437 MPa for cold compaction. Composite yield strengths are 607, 667, 1069, and 1172 MPa. Source thermal-mismatch contributions are only 2.7, 3.0, 3.8, and 5.3 MPa. TiC particle sizes are 4.848, 4.002, 3.584, and 1.335 micrometres; TiC fractions are 0.457, 0.457, 0.640, and 0.457 vol.%; KAM values are 0.444, 0.445, 0.628, and 0.622 degrees. The source concludes that thermal mismatch is not a significant contributor relative to grain refinement and secondary phases.",
